post_text: Good Afternoon, Let me take a moment to put some rumors to rest. Yes, the school was broken into last week. We are cooperating with the Franklin PD as much as we can. It just saddens me that anyone would feel it is ok to steal from a school. They helped themselves to some of the life skills items, as well as the pantry items we use to support our families. They also took quite a few of the tools we use for our fundraising. I wont go into the list so it does not interfere with any work the police are doing. Thank you all for your concerns. Keep an eye out!

post_text: Happy Summer Compass Families! It is official! We have coaches for the Robotics Team and the Chess Club. Robotics will be have two groups. One for 4-6th grade and one for 7-9th grade. We still need more people to assist. Please give your time to these students to help make this a success. Chess Club will be meeting one day a aweek after school (tbd) We could use more adults to assist there too. The school wide welcome back picnic is at Riverfront Park in Tilton on August 19th from 5-8. Come welcome the new familes in and the old families back. It is a great opportunity to meet your teachers. September 4th from 5-7pm is Compass's open house. Learn about what is going on in the classrooms as well as see what club opportunities are available for your student. Find out ways you can volunteer and make your school even better. Wear your sunglasses, our future is so bright! Thank You and Enjoy Your Day, The Director, Staff and Faculty at Compass Classical Academy

Third $36.86
